The paper proposes a new approach for multi-view clustering, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper focuses on integrating multi-view information in a partition space, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of graphs and spectral clustering, which are common techniques in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.CL and cs.MM.
